            <title>[JDK-8304836] Make MALLOC_MIN4 macro more robust</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8304836</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>In the file `src/java.base/share/native/libjava/jni_util.c`, there is a macro for calculating minimum buffer size `MALLOC_MIN4`. While all current uses of the MALLOC_MIN4 macro are with a parameter of jint type, the macro itself is parameter type agnostic. This check can be more strict &#8212;at no computational cost&#8212; and prevent mistakes if there were a future use with a data type greater than jint (i.e. jlong).</description>
